# 101. al-Qari\`ah: The Terrible Calamity

<span id="an_101_001">1</span> The Calamity!

<span id="an_101_002">2</span> What is the Calamity ?

<span id="an_101_003">3</span> Ah, what will convey unto thee what the
Calamity is!

<span id="an_101_004">4</span> A day wherein mankind will be as
thickly-scattered moths

<span id="an_101_005">5</span> And the mountains will become as carded
wool.

<span id="an_101_006">6</span> Then, as for him whose scales are heavy
(with good works),

<span id="an_101_007">7</span> He will live a pleasant life.

<span id="an_101_008">8</span> But as for him whose scales are light,

<span id="an_101_009">9</span> A bereft and Hungry One will be his
mother,

<span id="an_101_010">10</span> Ah, what will convey unto thee what she
is! -

<span id="an_101_011">11</span> Raging Fire.

